{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1050,"text":"It's time to start designing for our ears."},{"time":4841,"text":"Architects and designers tend to focus"},{"time":6921,"text":"exclusively on these."},{"time":8447,"text":"They use these to design with and they design for them,"},{"time":11561,"text":"which is why we end up sitting in restaurants that look"},{"time":13889,"text":"like this — (loud crowd noise) — and sound like this,"},{"time":15686,"text":"shouting from a foot away to try and be heard"},{"time":18233,"text":"by our dinner companion,"},{"time":19535,"text":"or why we get on airplanes -- (flight attendant announcements) -- which cost 200 million pounds,"},{"time":22758,"text":"with somebody talking through an old-fashioned telephone handset"},{"time":26601,"text":"on a cheap stereo system,"},{"time":28137,"text":"making us jump out of our skins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30790,"text":"We're designing environments that make us crazy. (Laughter)"},{"time":34174,"text":"And it's not just our quality of life which suffers."},{"time":36886,"text":"It's our health,"},{"time":38661,"text":"our social behavior, and our productivity as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42672,"text":"How does this work? Well, two ways."},{"time":44314,"text":"First of all, ambience. I have a whole TEDTalk about this."},{"time":47753,"text":"Sound affects us physiologically, psychologically,"},{"time":51184,"text":"cognitively and behaviorally all the time."},{"time":53384,"text":"The sound around us is affecting us"},{"time":55121,"text":"even though we're not conscious of it."},{"time":57443,"text":"There's a second way though, as well."},{"time":59199,"text":"That's interference. Communication requires sending"},{"time":62576,"text":"and receiving, and I have another whole TEDTalk"},{"time":66476,"text":"about the importance of conscious listening,"},{"time":68940,"text":"but I can send as well as I like,"},{"time":70974,"text":"and you can be brilliant conscious listeners."},{"time":73388,"text":"If the space I'm sending it in is not effective,"},{"time":76888,"text":"that communication can't happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79382,"text":"Spaces tend to include noise and acoustics."},{"time":81912,"text":"A room like this has acoustics, this one very good acoustics."},{"time":85612,"text":"Many rooms are not so good."},{"time":87780,"text":"Let me give you some examples from a couple of areas"},{"time":89811,"text":"which I think we all care about: health and education."},{"time":93284,"text":"(Hospital noises) When I was visiting my terminally ill father"},{"time":95516,"text":"in a hospital, I was asking myself,"},{"time":97548,"text":"how does anybody get well in a place that sounds like this?"},{"time":101685,"text":"Hospital sound is getting worse all the time."},{"time":103993,"text":"Noise levels in hospitals have doubled"},{"time":105999,"text":"in the last few years, and it affects not just the patients"},{"time":109603,"text":"but also the people working there."},{"time":111419,"text":"I think we would like for dispensing errors to be zero,"},{"time":115296,"text":"wouldn't we? And yet, as noise levels go up, so do"},{"time":118761,"text":"the errors in dispensing made by the staff in hospitals."},{"time":122315,"text":"Most of all, though, it affects the patients,"},{"time":125370,"text":"and that could be you, it could be me."},{"time":127578,"text":"Sleep is absolutely crucial for recovery."},{"time":129917,"text":"It's when we regenerate, when we rebuild ourselves,"},{"time":132957,"text":"and with threatening noise like this going on,"},{"time":135341,"text":"your body, even if you are able to sleep, your body"},{"time":138493,"text":"is telling you, \"I'm under threat. This is dangerous.\""},{"time":141536,"text":"And the quality of sleep is degraded, and so is our recovery."},{"time":144765,"text":"There are just huge benefits to come"},{"time":146917,"text":"from designing for the ears in our health care."},{"time":149954,"text":"This is an area I intend to take on this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152861,"text":"Education."},{"time":154826,"text":"When I see a classroom that looks like this,"},{"time":156422,"text":"can you imagine how this sounds?"},{"time":158299,"text":"I am forced to ask myself a question."},{"time":160630,"text":"(\"Do architects have ears?\") (Laughter)"},{"time":163207,"text":"Now, that's a little unfair. Some of my best friends"},{"time":165874,"text":"are architects. (Laughter) And they definitely do have ears."},{"time":168763,"text":"But I think sometimes they don't use them"},{"time":170828,"text":"when they're designing buildings. Here's a case in point."},{"time":173491,"text":"This is a 32-million-pound flagship academy school"},{"time":177182,"text":"which was built quite recently in the U.K. and designed"},{"time":179187,"text":"by one of Britain's top architects."},{"time":182334,"text":"Unfortunately, it was designed like a corporate"},{"time":184159,"text":"headquarters, with a vast central atrium"},{"time":186558,"text":"and classrooms leading off it with no back walls at all."},{"time":190832,"text":"The children couldn't hear their teachers."},{"time":192758,"text":"They had to go back in and spend 600,000 pounds"},{"time":195479,"text":"putting the walls in. Let's stop this madness"},{"time":198559,"text":"of open plan classrooms right now, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202621,"text":"It's not just these modern buildings which suffer."},{"time":206149,"text":"Old-fashioned classrooms suffer too."},{"time":208486,"text":"A study in Florida just a few years ago found"},{"time":210680,"text":"that if you're sitting where this photograph was taken"},{"time":212357,"text":"in the classroom, row four, speech intelligibility"},{"time":215557,"text":"is just 50 percent."},{"time":218008,"text":"Children are losing one word in two."},{"time":220208,"text":"Now that doesn't mean they only get half their education,"},{"time":222853,"text":"but it does mean they have to work very hard"},{"time":224565,"text":"to join the dots and understand what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227541,"text":"This is affected massively by reverberation time,"},{"time":230314,"text":"how reverberant a room is."},{"time":232214,"text":"In a classroom with a reverberation time of 1.2 seconds,"},{"time":235772,"text":"which is pretty common, this is what it sounds like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239468,"text":"(Inaudible echoing voice)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251772,"text":"Not so good, is it?"},{"time":253589,"text":"If you take that 1.2 seconds down to 0.4 seconds"},{"time":258048,"text":"by installing acoustic treatments, sound absorbing materials"},{"time":260996,"text":"and so forth, this is what you get."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263704,"text":"Voice: In language, infinitely many words can be written"},{"time":267565,"text":"with a small set of letters. In arithmetic,"},{"time":270437,"text":"infinitely many numbers can be composed"},{"time":272791,"text":"from just a few digits with the help of the simple zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276393,"text":"Julian Treasure: What a difference."},{"time":277957,"text":"Now that education you would receive,"},{"time":279797,"text":"and thanks to the British acoustician Adrian James"},{"time":282727,"text":"for those simulations. The signal was the same,"},{"time":285416,"text":"the background noise was the same."},{"time":286815,"text":"All that changed was the acoustics of the classroom"},{"time":289258,"text":"in those two examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290932,"text":"If education can be likened to watering a garden,"},{"time":293352,"text":"which is a fair metaphor, sadly, much of the water"},{"time":297519,"text":"is evaporating before it reaches the flowers,"},{"time":300575,"text":"especially for some groups,"},{"time":302607,"text":"for example, those with hearing impairment."},{"time":305983,"text":"Now that's not just deaf children. That could be any child"},{"time":308735,"text":"who's got a cold, glue ear, an ear infection,"},{"time":311170,"text":"even hay fever. On a given day, one in eight children"},{"time":313546,"text":"fall into that group, on any given day."},{"time":316362,"text":"Then you have children for whom English is a second language,"},{"time":319538,"text":"or whatever they're being taught in is a second language."},{"time":322474,"text":"In the U.K., that's more than 10 percent of the school population."},{"time":326058,"text":"And finally, after Susan Cain's wonderful TEDTalk in February,"},{"time":329718,"text":"we know that introverts find it very difficult to relate"},{"time":332934,"text":"when they're in a noisy environment doing group work."},{"time":335631,"text":"Add those up. That is a lot of children"},{"time":338292,"text":"who are not receiving their education properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340704,"text":"It's not just the children who are affected, though."},{"time":342940,"text":"(Noisy conversation) This study in Germany found"},{"time":344523,"text":"the average noise level in classrooms is 65 decibels."},{"time":348078,"text":"I have to really raise my voice to talk over 65 decibels"},{"time":352304,"text":"of sound, and teachers are not just raising their voices."},{"time":356088,"text":"This chart maps the teacher's heart rate"},{"time":358896,"text":"against the noise level."},{"time":361320,"text":"Noise goes up, heart rate goes up."},{"time":364027,"text":"That is not good for you."},{"time":366176,"text":"In fact, 65 decibels is the very level at which this big survey"},{"time":370256,"text":"of all the evidence on noise and health found that, that is"},{"time":373784,"text":"the threshold for the danger of myocardial infarction."},{"time":378491,"text":"To you and me, that's a heart attack."},{"time":381340,"text":"It may not be pushing the boat out too far to suggest"},{"time":384059,"text":"that many teachers are losing significant life expectancy"},{"time":388359,"text":"by teaching in environments like that day after day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392631,"text":"What does it cost to treat a classroom"},{"time":394687,"text":"down to that 0.4-second reverberation time?"},{"time":397457,"text":"Two and a half thousand pounds."},{"time":400191,"text":"And the Essex study which has just been done in the U.K.,"},{"time":403367,"text":"which incidentally showed that when you do this,"},{"time":405708,"text":"you do not just make a room that's suitable"},{"time":408071,"text":"for hearing-impaired children, you make a room"},{"time":409668,"text":"where behavior improves, and results improve significantly,"},{"time":414952,"text":"this found that sending a child out of area to a school"},{"time":418944,"text":"that does have such a room, if you don't have one,"},{"time":421575,"text":"costs 90,000 pounds a year."},{"time":425037,"text":"I think the economics are pretty clear on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427424,"text":"I'm glad that debate is happening on this."},{"time":429443,"text":"I just moderated a major conference in London"},{"time":432009,"text":"a few weeks ago called Sound Education,"},{"time":434058,"text":"which brought together top acousticians,"},{"time":435855,"text":"government people, teachers, and so forth."},{"time":437876,"text":"We're at last starting to debate this issue, and the benefits"},{"time":442075,"text":"that are available for designing for the ears in education,"},{"time":444775,"text":"unbelievable."},{"time":446586,"text":"Out of that conference, incidentally, also came"},{"time":449655,"text":"a free app which is designed to help children study"},{"time":452657,"text":"if they're having to work at home, for example,"},{"time":455028,"text":"in a noisy kitchen."},{"time":456620,"text":"And that's free out of that conference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459858,"text":"Let's broaden the perspective a little bit"},{"time":462809,"text":"and look at cities."},{"time":464220,"text":"We have urban planners."},{"time":466712,"text":"Where are the urban sound planners?"},{"time":469857,"text":"I don't know of one in the world, and the opportunity is there"},{"time":473064,"text":"to transform our experience in our cities."},{"time":475600,"text":"The World Health Organization estimates"},{"time":477707,"text":"that a quarter of Europe's population is having its sleep"},{"time":480291,"text":"degraded by noise in cities. We can do better than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484224,"text":"And in our offices, we spend a lot of time at work."},{"time":487053,"text":"Where are the office sound planners?"},{"time":489712,"text":"People who say, don't sit that team next to this team,"},{"time":491599,"text":"because they like noise and they need quiet."},{"time":493932,"text":"Or who say, don't spend all your budget on a huge screen"},{"time":496671,"text":"in the conference room,"},{"time":497614,"text":"and then place one tiny microphone"},{"time":499623,"text":"in the middle of a table for 30 people. (Laughter)"},{"time":502860,"text":"If you can hear me, you can understand me"},{"time":504979,"text":"without seeing me. If you can see me without hearing me,"},{"time":508104,"text":"that does not work."},{"time":510208,"text":"So office sound is a huge area, and incidentally,"},{"time":513424,"text":"noise in offices has been shown to make people"},{"time":515560,"text":"less helpful, less enjoy their teamwork,"},{"time":518183,"text":"and less productive at work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520704,"text":"Finally, we have homes. We use interior designers."},{"time":523757,"text":"Where are the interior sound designers?"},{"time":525992,"text":"Hey, let's all be interior sound designers,"},{"time":529332,"text":"take on listening to our rooms and designing sound"},{"time":532149,"text":"that's effective and appropriate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533667,"text":"My friend Richard Mazuch, an architect in London,"},{"time":536208,"text":"coined the phrase \"invisible architecture.\""},{"time":539094,"text":"I love that phrase."},{"time":540644,"text":"It's about designing, not appearance, but experience,"},{"time":545724,"text":"so that we have spaces that sound as good as they look,"},{"time":549332,"text":"that are fit for purpose, that improve our quality of life,"},{"time":552842,"text":"our health and well being, our social behavior"},{"time":556083,"text":"and our productivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557959,"text":"It's time to start designing for the ears."},{"time":561465,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":564295,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":565827,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}